      <hedline>
        <hl1>Jerusalem Under U.N.?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fay Dicker letter rejects suggestion in July 18 letter that central core of Old Jerusalem be international city under jurisdiction of United Nations</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In response to Karen Armstrong's ''No One People Owns Jerusalem'' (Op-Ed, July 16), a July 18 letter writer's suggestion that the central core of Old Jerusalem be an international city under the jurisdiction of the United Nations is a nonstarter.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In response to Karen Armstrong's ''No One People Owns Jerusalem'' (Op-Ed, July 16), a July 18 letter writer's suggestion that the central core of Old Jerusalem be an international city under the jurisdiction of the United Nations is a nonstarter.</p>
        <p>The United Nations is an entity that for decades has shown its antipathy toward Israel, passing numerous one-sided hostile resolutions and, until recently, barring Israel's participation in any regional grouping, excluding it from important committees. Still, Israel has been asked to forgo the chance to hold a seat on the Security Council.</p>
        <p>Such an arrangement for Jerusalem would be a disaster for Israel.</p>
        <p>FAY DICKER  Brooklyn, July 18, 2000</p>
      </block>
